	<div class="content">
		<blockquote class="restore">Blizzard tends to overestimate the raiding ability of the non-heroic raider. <br />
If you look at Elegon 10-man normal statistics on WoL, he's at 80% wipes. <br />
<br />
He's a roadblock to a lot of people (my guild included), and the fact that Garalon, Wind Lord and Amber-Shaper still sits at 87% wipes is pretty amazing. <br />
They have acknowledged the enrage timer problems in this tier, and there are apparently less of those in the next tier:<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_description">Quote:</div>
	<div class="bbcode_quote printable">
		<hr />
		
			<div>
				Originally Posted by <strong>Blizzard Gamebreaker interview</strong>
				
			</div>
			<div class="message">* Tier 14 had a few too many hard DPS checks on Normal difficulty, so in Tier 15 you should beat Normal difficulty by mastering the mechanics, not having a certain amount of DPS.<br />
* Complex mechanics and a very strict DPS check might be too much for a Normal difficulty encounter, as most players can't flawlessly perform their rotations and avoid standing in the fire.</div>
			
		<hr />
	</div>
</div>As an example, we had 13 tries on Imperial Vizier Zor'lok yesterday. In only ONE try did we make it to the last phase with 10 players alive. And I'm pretty sure that we'd burned the combat rez at that point in time.<br />
Yep, we have our share of really bad raiders. But in the previous expansions, we've been able to compensate for this by having excellent tanks/healers and a few exceptional DPS to pull people through.<br />
I'm sure that once we're decked out in 522 and 502 gear, it'll happen. It's just very, very far away at this point in time.</blockquote>
	</div>
